description: Supernova Energy, Inc. engages in the exploration and production of oil and gas properties primarily in Kansas. It has 87 oil, gas, and SWD wells with interests in 2,020 acres of leaseholds. The company holds a 50% working interest on the Monroe Lease, which has 2 producing wells with approximately 1200 feet deep. It is also involved in the exploration of precious minerals. The company was formerly known as Northumberland Resources, Inc. and changed its name to Supernova Energy, Inc. in October 2013. Supernova Energy, Inc. was founded in 2009 and is based in Rockville Centre, New York.
